pg 1003, #29.1

Creating an investment value calculator
Write a program that calculates the future value of an investment at a given
interest rate for a specified number of years. The formula for the calculation
is as follows:

    futureValue = investmentAmount * ((1 + monthlyInterestRate) ^ (years * 12))

Use a text fields for interest rate, investment amount, and years. Display the
future amount in a text field when the user clicks the Calculate button or
chooses Calculate from the Operation menu (see Figure 29.24 [1]). Show a
message dialog box when the user clicks the About menu item from the Help menu.

:[1] Figure 29.24
The user enters the investment amount, years, and interst rate to compute
future value.

